                <p>
                    The Computer Association of a college is typically a student-led organization or club dedicated to promoting and enhancing knowledge, skills, and activities related to computer science and information technology. Here's some detailed information about a Computer Association at a college:
                    <br><br><p><strong>Mission:</strong> Fosters interest and excellence in computer science and IT fields among students, creating a supportive community.</p>

                    <p><strong>Membership:</strong> Open to all students interested in computer-related disciplines, regardless of background or expertise.</p>
                
                    <p><strong>Activities:</strong> Organizes technical workshops, hackathons, guest lectures, networking events, and community projects.</p>
                
                    <p><strong>Leadership:</strong> Run by elected student leaders, including a president, vice president, treasurer, and secretary.</p>
                    
                    <p>A Computer Association enriches the college experience for students interested in computer science and IT, offering learning, collaboration, and community-building opportunities.</p>
